description:
Purchases of this book helped Linsner.com donate $10,000 to the American Red Cross following the events of September 11th.

This comic is is a personal account of 9/11 and how the events unfolded to Linsner himself and the days follow the events.

There is an extended written piece by Eva Hopkins called Homefires Burning on the last page.

Dawn appears as cover art and in crowd scenes.

Somewhere in Asia, aeons ago, stood the city. Even then it was older than any of its millions of residents could remember. Created as a bastion of peace, learning and human dignity, the huge, walled metropolis existed in blissful harmony since the beginning. Xian is a serious and dedicated student, living a life of ease and serenity in her beloved city.  
 
But now a serpent of corruption slithers in the shadows of this paradise. Now evil has set its sights on the city and its citizens, and a spreading dark stain of evil has begun to infest the city. Only Xian can be made ready to fight back!

volume.name: Megaton Man Meets The Uncatergorizable X-Thems

name: Meg 244

description:
Genevieve arrives at the Castle of the Holy Grail, little knowing the danger that lurks within. She finally lays eyes on the grisly horror of the true Holy Grail, unaware Lorraine's Imperial Guard have captured Julien the night before. Her days as a duchess might be coming to a very abrupt and unpleasant end!

Isabelle has escaped her father's men, but she is weak and desperate. Can she rally to save Julien and take on her father? She has a plan . . . and the duke, at the height of his power, surrounded by the might and majesty of the Castle of the Holy Grail, might not be as safe as he thinks!
name: Fallen Angel

description: Harada has captured Faith! Finally, he reveals the secret machinations that have controlled her life and his plan for her future. Will Faith go along and leave behind everything she has known forever... or will she resist!
name: No Tomorrow , Part 3 of 3: "The Truth"

description: This is the big one! Space agent extraordinaire Johnny Raygun is joined by just about every character who has appeared in the book as they square off to take on the menacing Darkmind! Darkmind has made his presence known in previous issues, moving behind the scenes to eliminate every other villain he can find!

Sam is in a funk after Mira tells him she only wants to be friends, so the boys of the Detention Squad try cheer him up with a night out. But what's supposed to be just a little after curfew extracurricular fun turns violent when they run into one of Ax's Rogue Harbingers -- the sadistic Spikeman!

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".
name: Pierced Hearts

description:
As Faith finally resurfaces, Simon, Sam, Butch and Veronica are shocked to discover her sudden transformation. But as the Eggbreakers descend on our heroes, Mira's musings on her role in the foundation may have deadly consequences.

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".
name: Renegades

description:
The outlaw Taniguchi is the bounty of the day, and hunters Gen and Stray Dog once again find themselves joining forces to better their chances of catching their common prey. Agreeing that the first to capture Taniguchi should receive the lion's share of the reward, the two part ways in an attempt to cover as much territory as possible.

Yet when Gen is the first to find the outlaw, he discovers that-much to his dismay-Taniguchi is essentially a decent guy, undeserving of death! What will this money-loving, sentimental cutthroat do?
name: The Outlaw

description: Toyo Harada has set the deadly and mysterious being known only as the Harbinger on Faith Herbert's trail. Can Faith and her fellow Harbinger Foundation runaways hope to stand against a being with all their Harbinger abilities and more at his command?
name: The Pursuit Of Happiness

description:
It's the end of an era as Faith and her fellow rebels stand against the mysterious Harbinger in a final confrontation that will see one of them dead!

Final Issue!

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".

Death of:

- Anvil (Samuel Coleman)
name: Postcards

volume.name: The New Age Tales Of Alternative Adventures

description: What happens when our hero takes a good long look in the mirror...and sees The Golden Age Sentry! PLUS, It's an invasion! No---not that kind of invasion; it's a British music invasion. But the dance party grinds to a sudden halt when the Crick-Hits are kidnapped, and it's all tunnels lead to Rome as the Golden Guardian of good teams up with the Blonde Phantom journeying deep within the Earth to do battle against a seemingly unstoppable army of monsters and their rather tyrannical leader.
name: The Golden-Age Sentry; I Want to Hold Your Band!

description: The Spirit hits Cambodia! Somebody is murdering the former members of an Army platoon, one by one, and the trail leads back to Phnom Penh! A noir murder mystery in the Spirit style!
name: Veterans' Benefits

description: Comics legend Karl (MARVEL APES) Kesel teams with Jesse (GOOD AS LILY) Hamm for a twisted tale of a boy and his dog just trying to stay alive while wending their way through a land of zombies! Plus, John Schnepp treats us to "Nails," a story of zombie causality that will get us a bunch of angry letters from the American Tobacco Company.
name: Backbiter; Lights Out; Ink Stains

description: With great power, there must also come great responsibility — and when those in power abuse it, it’s the people’s responsibility to remove them. The year is 1933, and New York City is not-so-secretly run by corrupt politicians, crooked cops, big businesses…and suave gangland bosses like New York’s worst, the Goblin. But when a fateful spider-bite gives the young rabble-rouser Peter Parker the power to fight the mobster who killed his Uncle Ben, will even that be enough? It’s a tangled web of Great Depression pulp, with familiar faces like you’ve never seen them before! By “Hardboiled” David Hine, Fabrice “The Spider” Sapolsky and Carmine “Carbine” Di Giandomenico!

The final showdown of Peter Stanchek and Toyo Harada happens here, only in this double-sized issue! Peter has reached the inner sanctum of the Harbinger Foundation and will finally have his revenge on the man who ruined his life. But it's not until they come face to face that Peter will realize just how strong of a hold Harada has on him...and his powers.

Death of:

  • Rock
  • Screen
name: Twilight Of The Eighth Day - Part Three: Armageddon

description:
From out of the ashes, here comes an all-new Harbinger team! In the wake of the decisive battle between Peter Stanchek and Toyo Harada, Faith "Zephyr" Herbert has re-joined the Harbinger Foundation! But will she be accepted ? or singled out as a "renegade murderer" for her crimes against her new masters?

1st appearances:

  • Anvil (Samual Coleman)
  • Sonix (Gaylord Butch MacFaddin)
  • Amazon (Beatrice Lewis)
  • Microwave (Malik Williams)
  • Tyger (Mira Choudhury)
name: The Other Side

description: After a rocky start, Faith "Zephyr" Herbert is becoming acquainted with her new classmates in the Harbinger Foundation. Shacked up in a remote mountaintop cabin, the Harbingers-in-training encounter a nightmarish monster. Can these super-powered teens band together to defend themselves ? or will their first team mission be their last?
name: Cabin Fever

description: Toyo Harada is dying! But will happen to the Harbinger Foundation? And do any of Harada's studnets have the power, visionand fortitude to lead his students into a new era? The future starts? now!
name: Heal Thyself

description: A new love interest is introduced as Zorro continues to be hounded by the military men that he's made to look so foolish and incompetent.

Stronghold and Livewire have been brought back to the Harbinger Foundation. When Livewire turns to Faith for help breaking her and Eddie out, a crisis of conscience brings her to call the Detention Squad into action! But is it already too late?

VP6 HARDCorps bonus card (Valiant Era) originally included.
name: Truth And Consequences

description:
After the terrible defeat of the X-Men at the hands of the Emperor Vulcan, a new future emerged for the Shi'ar Empire. And the first step in Vulcan's destiny is the expansion of his empire. That means to take over the galaxy and destroy everyone in his path.

In the meantime, the Galactic Council gathers to discuss the aftermath of the Annihilation wave and the lack of aid of the Shi'ar during the armageddon and also their aggressive expansion throughout the galaxy. Nevertheless, all hope to reason with the mighty Shi'ar Empire will find no echo as they are blinded with Vulcan's promise to regain their past glory.

But not everything is lost. The remaining forces of the Starjammers led by Lilicandra are using guerrilla warfare to hurt the Shi''ar army in order to find their fallen comrades. But Vulcan placed his brother, Polaris and the rest of the Starjammers on the very edge of the Empire where they are victims of the more vicious acts of torture. Summers vs Summers, and Havok has still one ace up to his sleeves.
name: Part 1

description: With Toyo Harada in a coma following his climactic confrontation with Peter Stanchek, this is the Omen Enterprises and their elite H.A.R.D. Corps' best chance to finally take him out! The only thing in their way? Faith Herbert and the Detention Squad!
name: Bad Omen Part 1

description: Toyo Harada is taking stock of his foundation. Will Faith and her friends be able to convince him to keep the Detention Squad together? And what will Harada do when he discovers what Kuramoto's been doing to his students in his absence?
name: Bad Omen Part 3: Last Rites

description: Harada has a lot to account for when the Eternal Warrior visits the Harbinger Foundation to look in on his friends Stronghold and Livewire. But things get even more heated when Stunner finds out that Blast has been lying to her...
name: Incandescent Expectations

description: Faith Herbert and friends are on a crosscountry trip to New York. But when their car breaks down in rural Ohio, they'll find themselves facing a terrifying creature of necromantic energy conjured up by Master Darque!
name: Total Eclipse

person_credits.name: Jeff Smith
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: "Proceeds from the sale of this comic support Literacy Volunteers of Chicago."

Siryn goes into labor three weeks early. Could this be the second mutant born since M-Day? Either way, the U.S. government isn't going to sit idle while it happens. Can Rictor and the mother-to-be fend them off? They'll have to, since X-Factor and Longshot are busy fighting an army of Darwins!!
name: Smart Business

description:
CONCLUSION TO “THE DEATH OF MARC SPECTOR”

Norman Osborn ain’t fooling around no more. He’s brought out his big gun. It’s Moon Knight versus Bullseye -- and only one will survive. For real.
name: The Death Of Marc Spector, Chapter Five

description: Mulder and Scully race to uncover the truth about the apparent suicide of a government scientist. All evidence points to it being nothing more than a case of one man choosing to end his own life, but Mulder is convinced the evidence isn't revealing everything. For Agent Fox Mulder, uncovering the truth is literally a case of life or death.
